					<p class="comment-author">
						<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/d870c416e232996cda089cc60cad90b1?s=32&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D32&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-32' height='32' width='32' />						<span>Tiffany</span> <em>said:</em>					</p>
					<p class="comment-date">
						<a href="http://downtonabbeycooks.wordpress.com/2012/02/07/tea-tuesdays-making-tea-and-guilt-free-fruit-scones/#comment-4069"><time pubdate datetime="2013-07-10T18:09:00+00:00">July 10, 2013 at 6:09 pm</time></a>					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="comment-text">
					<p>I just tried the scones and they were AMAZING!! Hands down the best scone recipe I&#8217;ve made yet! </p>
<p>I went ahead and subbed buttermilk for the milk, and added lemon zest and frozen wild blueberries. Super easy to adapt the recipe and have fantastic results. To cut the prep time I also zipped the butter into the flour with the little food processor- I was elbow-deep in baking these and your Gougères to spend the time hand cutting the dough. </p>
<p>Now all that&#8217;s left is waiting for my clotted cream to cool, and slightly glazing the scones with a lemon zest glaze. </p>
<p>Will definitely follow your recipes and pass on the word of your great blog!</p>
